&#039;Slime And Reason&#039; is the follow-up to 2006&#039;s &#039;Alternately Deep&#039; from London- 
based rapper Roots Manuva. Roots aka Rodney Smith has built a solid 
reputation as one of the best hip hop artists in the UK, mainly through his 
ability to embracemany different styles while maintaining a high standard of 
lyrical content and delivery. With more focus on electronicsand dub than his 
previous effort, which employed a live band feel, this is another example of 
the artist&#039;s diversity. Singles include &#039;Buff Nuff&#039;.
